Hi Carlos,

I've reviewed the logs from today's tool ejection incident on CNC Machine X (MCH-X001). 
This is the third failure this month for this machine (June 3 spindle overheating, June 12 coolant pump impeller crack).

Mike mentioned that the clamp pressure dropped immediately before the tool ejected. We found a micro-leak at hydraulic junction B7. We need to check if the high vibrations from the Z-axis misalignment (logged on June 8) contributed to loosening the Parker H-series junction seals.

Please make sure we replace the seals on all similar CNC lines on Floor East (Line-3) during next week's PM cycle.

